TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {21671=2013|Stats: Played in all 17 games, starting 14…Made her first career start in the season opener against Bryant…Finished the season third on the team in both points and goals, totaling seven points on three goals and one assist…Scored here first career goal in the Bears’ 4-3 win over Colgate on September 22 … Named to the Ivy League Weekly Honor Roll after scoring the overtime winner in Brown’s 2-1 upset win over #14 Louisville on October 13…also scored against Holy Cross…Registered a defensive save in the Bears’ Ivy League matchup against Penn., 23181=Personal: The daughter of Craig and Lorena Angus, Katarina has one brother, Eddie, a member of the Brown Class of 2014 … Enjoys skiing, tennis and golf … Undecided on a concentration. , 24980=2013, 22492=Before Brown: A three-year starter at Collingwood School in West Vancouver, British Columbia, Angus helped to lead Collingwood to the BC Provincial Championship as a senior captain … Collingwood also won silver at the Provincial Championship in 2011 and gold in 2010 … Was a three-time North Shore Secondary School First Team All-Star … Played on Team BC at Canadian National Championship as a U16 and U18 … Also attended Canadian Women’s Junior National Team Development Camp … Member of Canadian National Women’s Target 2017 Team … Received Honors in Service, Academics, Athletics and Arts all four years of high school., 62003=Brown University Athletics | 235 Hope St. Box 1932 | Providence, RI 02912}
